<document>
    <header>
        <title>ServoMaster: Metadata: <code>servo/precision</code></title>
    </header>
    <body>
        
        <section>
            <title>Definition</title>
            
            <p>
            
                <code>servo/precision</code> <em>property</em> contains the
                number of physical steps available between logical
                <code>0.0</code> and <code>1.0</code> positions.
                
            </p>
            <p>
            
                 Please note that this property may be dynamic for some
                 controllers, for example <link
                 href="site:phidget_quad">QuadServo</link>, <link
                 href="site:phidget_servo8">AdvancedServo</link>, and <link
                 href="site:pololu">Pololu</link> family.
                 
            </p>
            <p>
                 
                 As a rule of thumb, if the <link
                 href="site:meta_servo_range_min"><code>servo/range/min</code></link>
                 and <link
                 href="site:meta_servo_range_max"><code>servo/range/max</code></link>
                 properties are writeable, this property's value may
                 dynamically change.
                
            </p>
            
        </section>
        
    </body>
</document>
